result.execSummary:
The defendant Alesa Marie Dae Hamby was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

2:08 PM Defendant Alesa Marie Dae Hamby in court.  Attorney Mark J Gumz in court for Alesa Marie Dae Hamby.  Prosecuting attorney Clifford C. Burdon in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Atty Burdon states plea agreement. Defendant to enter plea to Ct 2.  State will move to dismiss and read in Cts 1, 3 & 4.  Atty Gumz agrees.
Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge. Defendant enters No Contest plea to Ct 2.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently. Court relies on the criminal complaint for a factual basis. BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty of Ct 2 and orders the judgment of conviction as of today's date. Counts 1, 3 & 4 are ordered dismissed and read-in.
Counsel make sentencing statements. Defendant makes statement.

BY THE COURT:
Ct 2:  Sentence withheld, defendant placed on probation for period of 12 months with conditions:
*Complete Anger Management counseling
*Any other counseling or treatment deemed appropriate by the agent
*No violent or abusive contact with Victims 1 & 2
*Pay costs of $443.00
*Submit DNA sample
*2 days credit if probation is revoked
